  - paragraph: Automatically run code in response to database changes, user events, or on preset intervals.
  - img "atlas_data_api"
  - heading "Data API" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Easily integrate Atlas data into your cloud apps and services over HTTPS with a flexible API.
  - img "atlas_graphql"
  - heading "GraphQL API" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Access Atlas data from any standard GraphQL client with an API that generates based on your data’s schema.
  - img "realm_sync"
  - heading "Device Sync" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Gather, sync, and analyze data from your mobile apps and devices in real-time with built-in sync.
  - img "realm_sdk"
  - heading "Web SDK" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Securely connect browser-based applications to Atlas data and interact with services such as Functions.
  - img "realm_user_authorization"
  - heading "Authentication" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Configure one or more authentication providers for your application including AppleID, Google, and Facebook via OAuth 2.0.
  - img "general_security"
  - heading "Data Access Rules" [level=3]
  - paragraph: Define data types, control what users can read and write, and validate data changes.
